title: 17 northeast Indiana students make spring Dean's List
title_page: Saint Mary's College: 17 northeast Indiana students make spring Dean's List
maintext:
Seventeen northeast Indiana students have been named to the spring Dean’s List at Saint Mary’s College, the college has announced.
To earn the honor, a student must achieve a grade-point average of 3.6 or higher on a 4.0 scale, have at least 12 graded credit hours, no incompletes and no grades lower than a C, the college in Notre Dame, Indiana, said in a statement.
Area students on the list are:
Avilla: Regina Novy; Fort Wayne: Sarah Braun, Monica Eggebrecht, Kaitlin Emmett, Sabrina Hollis, Katherine Hollman, Ashley Nicholas, MacKenzie North, Marisabel Sanchez, Anna Slusser, Haley Stronczek, Isabella Wiseman; Huntington: Evelyn Cornwell, Emily Klepper; New Haven: Kylee Hillmann, Victoria Tippmann; Syracuse: Emma Larson
